  "text": "Taken together, we propose that an optimal enhancement of SKN-1 activity in proper time-frame may enhance immune responses and delay immunosenescence without compromising longevity. In recent years, C. elegans has become a versatile model not only for studying innate immunity, host-pathogen interactions, but for testing pharmacological interventions in drug discovery [CITATION_1] . The results presented herein may prompt studies on drugs targeting SKN-1/Nrf2 to modulate the innate immune response. In conclusion, our findings indicate an intricate regulation of innate immunity by SKN-1, and link pathogenic stress signaling to xenobiotic and oxidative stress responses.",
